title: Velopark Idaho State STXC and Dual
2010 Swica CRIT Series Boise Velo Women/ Team Ridg
All Gravity #2
description:
Silver Mountains opening weekend will be the second event in the 2011 All Gravity Series…  We’re still waiting on the snow to melt off the top of the mountain, but that won’t stop us.  Race will start mid mountain (shortening the times from 14-20 minutes down to 7-10).

Both events will be DH races!

Helmet cam videos soon to come!

Online registration open until June 16th,  there is a $5 late fee for registration at event.

USA CYCLING RELEASE FORM (this can also be filled out at the event)

Online Registration

Registration:
Friday 2-6
Saturday 7:30-12
Sunday 7:30-12

Practice:
Saturday 7:30-12:30
Sunday 7:30-12:30

Race will start at 2pm Saturday and 1pm Sunday, and is USA Cycling sanctioned.

Cost of race is $20/day
Day licenses will be $5/day (one license for each day of riding, including Friday practice)
Register online by June 16, 2011 – you can register online without making payment (select “cash/check/card at race”)
After June 16, 2011 there will be a $5 late registration fee. Racers may register online until 6pm June 16 and registration will also be open on both race days.
Lift tickets will be available for purchase at event.

All riders will be required to have a license for practice AND race, whether it is a single day license purchased or a year license.
All racers will also be required to ride in a full face helmet.
course: The course is weather/snow permitting...  And will be determined the final days leading up to the event, expect it to be fast.
registration:
Register online at allgravityseries.com or on site, there will be a $5 late fee after June 16th.

Lift tickets will be sold seperately at the price of $27/day...  There may be a 2 day discount.
directions: Registration will be located in the village at the Gondola Base.

title: 2011 Town to Summit Hill Climb
course: Race starts at the Elephant\'s Perch in Ketchum.  Neutral Start behind the Sun Valley Fire Department fire truck until the old Golf Pro shop.  Race is to the top of Trail Creek summit.  The last 3k plus is on dirt, so you need to decide if you are riding a road bike, a cross bike, or a mountain bike.
registration: Walk in Registration at the Perch.
